==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oxalantin
<hw>Ox`a*lan"tin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Alloxantin</er>, by transposition of letters.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white crystalline nitrogenous substance
(<chform>C6H4N4O5</chform>) obtained by the reduction of parabanic acid;
-- called also <altname>leucoturic acid</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oxalate</ent>⟦br⟧
